Incident Severity Classification. Four level cards with color coding: 1) LOW (Green): Single bad output, no harm -> Fix in next release. 2) MEDIUM (Yellow): Systematic bias, repeated errors -> Temp feature disable, patch. 3) HIGH (Orange): Privacy violation, discrimination -> Immediate shutdown, authority notification, PR. 4) CRITICAL (Red): Personal harm, rights violation -> Full system shutdown, legal action. Escalation arrows. Response time SLAs: Low 1 week, Medium 24h, High 1h, Critical 15min. German labels.